main event: A sighting report of a transient light described as a meteor observed over Cedar Rapids, Iowa on August 9, 1965.
interesting points: The object was slightly larger than a kitchen match head and had an incandescent white color,The sighting lasted for approximately 4 to 6 seconds,The object moved in a straight flight from NE to SW without any sound or discernable features,The observer was a 25-year-old science teacher,The weather conditions were clear with 5 percent cirrus cloud cover during the sighting.
sighted object: transient light with incandescent white color
